&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;blame&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commend&lt;/strong&gt;: To praise or express approval of someone or something. (प्रशंसा करना: किसी की या किसी चीज की प्रशंसा या अनुमोदन करना।)&amp;nbsp;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The teacher &lt;strong&gt;commended &lt;/strong&gt;the students for their hard work.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blame&lt;/strong&gt;: To hold responsible for something. (दोष देना: किसी चीज़ के लिए ज़िम्मेदार ठहराना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt; The manager &lt;strong&gt;blamed&lt;/strong&gt; the employee for the mistake.&lt;/em&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#39;s check the meaning of the other words:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promote&lt;/strong&gt;: To advance in rank or position. (प्रोन्नत करना: पद पर आगे बढ़ना।)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The company &lt;strong&gt;promoted&lt;/strong&gt; him to the position of manager. (&lt;/em&gt;उदाहरण : कंपनी ने उसे प्रबंधक के पद पर पदोन्नत किया।&lt;em&gt;)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endorse&lt;/strong&gt;: To support or approve publicly. (समर्थन: सार्वजनिक रूप से समर्थन या अनुमोदन करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The celebrity endorsed&amp;nbsp;a new brand of skincare products.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Praise&lt;/strong&gt;: To express approval or admiration of someone or something. (स्तुति करना: किसी चीज़ की स्वीकृति या प्रशंसा व्यक्त करना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The audience &lt;strong&gt;praised&lt;/strong&gt; the singer for his incredible performance.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is-&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Anomaly&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Aberration&lt;/span&gt;(noun): a temporary change from the typical or usual way of behaving.(व्यवहार के विशिष्ट या सामान्य तरीके से एक अस्थायी परिवर्तन।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;Example:&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I&amp;#39;m sorry I&amp;#39;m late - I had a mental &lt;strong&gt;aberration &lt;/strong&gt;and forgot we had a meeting today.&lt;/em&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Anomaly&lt;/span&gt;(noun)&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;something that is unusual enough to be noticeable or seem strange.(ऐसा कुछ जो ध्यान देने योग्य या अजीब लगने के लिए पर्याप्त असामान्य हो।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The government does computer checks of tax returns to find &lt;strong&gt;anomalies &lt;/strong&gt;that might indicate fraud.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the word &lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;nomaly&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the most appropriate word similar&amp;nbsp;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Aberration.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of other options:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Ordinary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective): not different or special or unexpected in any way; usual.(किसी भी तरह से अलग या विशेष या अप्रत्याशित नहीं; सामान्य।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;an &lt;strong&gt;ordinary &lt;/strong&gt;neighbourhood&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Usual&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(adjective): normal; happening, done, or used most often. (सामान्य; हो रहा है, किया गया है, या सबसे अधिक बार उपयोग किया जाता है।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I went to bed at my &lt;strong&gt;usual &lt;/strong&gt;time.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Norm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;(noun): an accepted standard or a way of behaving or doing things that most people agree with. (एक स्वीकृत मानक या व्यवहार करने या काम करने का एक तरीका जिससे अधिकांश लोग सहमत हैं।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Europe&amp;#39;s varied cultural, political, and ethical &lt;strong&gt;norms.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;The ordinary members&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The given idiom &amp;#39;the rank and file&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;the &lt;strong&gt;ordinary workers&lt;/strong&gt; in a company or the ordinary members of an organization, and not the leaders.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The &lt;strong&gt;rank and file&lt;/strong&gt; is/are unhappy with the president&amp;#39;s decision.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;With the given meaning and example sentence above, we are sure that &amp;#39;rank and file&amp;#39; means&lt;strong&gt; ordinary members.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;out and out&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means complete or thorough. (पूरी तरह से)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He is an &lt;strong&gt;out and out&lt;/strong&gt; supporter of the new policy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Thorough&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;means complete with regard to every detail; not superficial or partial. (संपूर्ण)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She conducted a&lt;strong&gt; thorough&lt;/strong&gt; investigation before publishing the report.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;out and out&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is best expressed by the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;thorough.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;thorough&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deadly against&lt;/strong&gt; (सख्त खिलाफ): Strongly opposed to something.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He is deadly against the proposed changes in the law.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In favour of&lt;/strong&gt; (समर्थन में): Supporting or approving of something.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She is in favour of the new environmental regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No more&lt;/strong&gt; (अब और नहीं): Not existing or happening anymore.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The old building is no more; it was demolished last year.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;forfeit&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ACQUISITION means&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;an asset or object bought or obtained, typically by a library or museum. (&lt;strong&gt;आमतौर पर किसी पुस्तकालय या संग्रहालय द्वारा खरीदी या प्राप्त की गई संपत्ति या वस्तु।)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The legacy will be used for new &lt;strong&gt;acquisitions&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The marked option &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;forfeit&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means&amp;nbsp;lost or surrendered as a penalty for wrongdoing. (&lt;strong&gt;गलत काम के लिए दंड के रूप में खोना या (संपत्ति या अधिकार या विशेषाधिकार) से वंचित होना।)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:- &lt;em&gt;Those unable to meet their taxes were liable to &lt;strong&gt;forfeit &lt;/strong&gt;their estates.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;Hence, we can conclude that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;the most appropriate antonym of the &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;ACQUISITION&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;forfeit&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;prize:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;a thing given as a reward to the winner of a competition or in recognition of outstanding achievement.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;strong&gt;पुरस्कार&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;addition:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;the action or process of adding something to something else. &lt;strong&gt;(किसी चीज़ में कुछ जोड़ने की क्रिया या प्रक्रिया।)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;recovery:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;a return to a normal state of health, mind, or strength.&amp;nbsp;(&lt;strong&gt;स्वास्थ्य, मन या शक्ति की सामान्य स्थिति में वापसी।)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
